######################################
######### COORDINATION ###############
######################################

# Ken, "and", is used to connect items which can be freely arranged, 
# stated in eirher order without affecting the intended semantics of
# the utterance. It may cordinate words, clauses. or entire sentences
Source: a:492
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination}
Ti      aso ken pusa
ti      aso ken pusa
CORE.SG dog and cat
`The dog and cat`

# Ket "and, and then", is mostly used to introduce successive nominal
# concepts or clauses. Unlike phrases or words that may be conncected 
# with ken, the order of consituents connected by ket may not be interchanged.
# Unlike ken, ket may not be used to conjoin parallelevents.
Source: a:492
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination}
Naglualokami          ket nagkantakami
n-ag-lualo=kami       ket n-ag-kanta=kami
PF-AF-pray=1PL.ABS.EXCL and PF-AF-sing=1PL.ABS.EXCL
'We prayed and sang`

# Coordination of pronoun and (proper) noun
Source: a:492
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {coordination}
Napankami           ken ti      lalaki.
na-pan=kami         ken ti      lalaki
PF-go=1PL.ABS.EXCL and CORE.SG boy
'The boy and I went.'


