# A properly formed 'what' question in which the interrogative
# is followed by 'ti' and a verb with an ergative enclitic pronoun:
Source: a:430
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ti      ginatangmo
ania ti      gatang-{in}=mo
what CORE.SG buy-{PF.GF}=2SG.ERG
'What did you buy?'

# Another 'what' question following the same pattern, but with the
# ergative enclitic on a glossed adjective.
Source: a:431
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ti      dakesmo
ania ti      dakes=mo
what CORE.SG bad=2SG.ERG
'What's wrong with you?'

# An incorrectly formed question where 'ti' is omitted before an encliticized word.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wh}
Ania ginatangmo
ania gatang-{in}=mo
what buy-{PF.GF}=2SG.ERG
'What did you buy?'

# A 'who' question formed similarly to the above questions.
Source: a:435
Vetted: s
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wh}
Sino ti      amam?
sino ti	    ama=mo
who  CORE.SG father=2SG.ERG
'Who is your father?'

# A 'who' question with absolutive enclitic pronoun on the verb.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {wh}
Sino ti      nakitaka?
sino ti      na-kita=ka
who  CORE.SG PF.GF-see=2SG.ABS
'Who saw you?'

######################################
######### Matrix yes-no questions ####
######################################

# Yes-no questions are indicated primarily by intonation alone, which is
# outside the scope of the grammar we're building, but they can also be
# expressed optionally by a second-position enclitic 'kadi' which appears
# After the first constituent of a sentence or clause.

# Week 6
# Example of a yes-no question with 'kadi'.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {yn}
Nalukmeg  kadi   ti      lalaki?
na-lukmeg kadi   ti      lalaki
ADJ-fat   QUES   CORE.SG boy
‘Is the boy fat?’

# Week 6
# Example of a yes-no question with 'kadi' after an encliticized adjective.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {yn}
Napigsaka          kadi?
na-pigsa=ka        kadi
ADJ-strong=2SG.ABS QUES
'Are you strong?'

# Week 6
# Example of a yes-no question with 'kadi' after an adjective with unmarked
# 3rd-person absolutive pronoun.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {yn}
Nalabaga         kadi?
na-labaga        kadi
ADJ-red(3SG.ABS) QUES
'Is it red?'

# Week 6
# Example of a yes-no question with 'kadi' after an encliticized noun.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {yn}
Amaka          kadi?
ama=ka	       kadi
father=2SG.ABS QUES
'Are you a father?'

# Week 6
# Ungrammatical example of 'kadi' in sentence-final position
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: u
Phenomena: {yn}
Nalukmeg  ti      lalaki kadi?
na-lukmeg ti      lalaki kadi
ADJ-fag   CORE.SG boy    QUES
'Is the boy fat?'

