# Week 5
# Grammatical sentence that should parse, but not as a possessive construction.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {wo}
Nagkita    ti      babai iti    sabong.
n-ag-kita  ti      babai iti    sabong
PF-AF-kita CORE.SG girl  OBL.SG flower
'The girl saw the flower.'

# Week 5
# Ambiguous sentence with one possessive parse and one agent-patient parse.
# The correct parse is the agent-patient configuration; the current state of
# the grammar also generates a non-preferred parse in which the girl is the
# possessor and the flower is the possessum.
Source: author
Vetted: f
Judgment: g
Phenomena: {poss}
Nakita     ti      babai ti      sabong.
na-kita    ti      babai ti      sabong
PF.GF-kita CORE.SG girl  CORE.SG flower
'The girl saw the flower.'

